        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 10:30PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Atwood, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Atwood around 1035 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
